# Known divergence: pgTAP's prepared/execute assertion variants fail through
# multigateway because SQL-level PREPARE is gateway-managed BY DESIGN.
#
# throwtap.sql runs `PREPARE meow AS ...` and then asserts that
# throws_ok('meow', ...) / lives_ok('EXECUTE meow') behave like their plain-SQL
# variants. multigateway stores SQL-level PREPARE in the gateway's consolidator
# under a canonical name; the backend session never sees a statement named
# `meow` (see go/services/multigateway/planner/execute_unwrap.go). pgTAP runs
# these via `EXECUTE meow` INSIDE a plpgsql function body, which the gateway
# cannot see or rewrite, so the backend raises "prepared statement does not
# exist" and the four assertions fail.
#
# Only these four assertions exercise that pattern; the other 93 assertions in
# the file pass and stay verified. The sibling files whose entire subject is
# this pattern (performs_ok, performs_within, resultset, valueset) abort their
# wrapping transaction on the first such error and are excluded instead
# (ExcludeGlobs on the pgtap spec in extensions.go).
--- a
+++ b
@@ -17,9 +17,15 @@
 ok 15 - single-argument form should pass
 ok 16 - single-argument form should have the proper description
 ok 17 - single-argument form should have the proper diagnostics
-ok 18 - prepared statement & errcode should pass
+not ok 18 - prepared statement & errcode should pass
+# Failed test 18: "prepared statement & errcode should pass"
+# have: false
+# want: true
 ok 19 - prepared statement & errcode should have the proper description
-ok 20 - execute & errcode should pass
+not ok 20 - execute & errcode should pass
+# Failed test 20: "execute & errcode should pass"
+# have: false
+# want: true
 ok 21 - execute & errcode should have the proper description
 ok 22 - invalid errcode should fail
 ok 23 - invalid errcode should have the proper description
@@ -29,9 +35,15 @@
 ok 27 - throws_ok diagnostics should have the proper description
 ok 28 - throws_ok diagnostics should have the proper diagnostics
 ok 29 - lives_ok() should work
-ok 30 - lives_ok(prepared) should pass
+not ok 30 - lives_ok(prepared) should pass
+# Failed test 30: "lives_ok(prepared) should pass"
+# have: false
+# want: true
 ok 31 - lives_ok(prepared) should have the proper description
-ok 32 - lives_ok(execute) should pass
+not ok 32 - lives_ok(execute) should pass
+# Failed test 32: "lives_ok(execute) should pass"
+# have: false
